0 This could have been a very good film , if I had been able to watch it . The hand held camera was very bouncy . From the opening credits I was worried . Several of us watching it felt very nauseous by the end . But we did stay until the end because it was such a charming and interesting film , giving some insight to the young pop culture in South Africa . The black and white film did enhance the artful feeling of it . The acting seemed very authentic . Some of the dialog was a little hard to understand , but a theater full of non - South Africans seemed to find most of it funny . If you get motion sickness at all though , you may seriously consider skipping this film . It 's quaint , but not worth the nausea .
